<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,679,1475]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,323,1346,1371]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant, 1916" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1916" box="[661,985,1347,1371]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[661,684,1348,1371]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[699,807,1347,1371]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">orientalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Distant" box="[821,977,1347,1371]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" refString="Distant, W. L. (1916) The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Rhyncbola. Vol, VI, Homoptera: appendix. Taylor and Francis, Fleet Street, Red Lion Court, London. 248 pp." type="book" year="1916">
Distant, 
<number box="[917,977,1347,1371]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="1916.0">1916</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter one by the tapering apical part of the aedeagus, shorter tips of styles and darker coloration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,679,1475]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,336,1417,1441]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name is derived from the Latin word “ 
<emphasis box="[979,1064,1416,1440]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">adustus</emphasis>
”, indicating that the body coloration is black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
